examples.content:
Chop 1/4 medium onion. Chop 1/4 tomato. Chop 1 green chilli. Peel 2 garlic cloves. Mince peeled garlic cloves. Chop 1 tsp cilantro. Heat 2 tbsp oil in a heavy-bottomed or nonstick pan, and add chopped onions and 1/3 tsp salt. Saute the onions on medium heat until they are soft and translucent. Add garlic and chilli to the pan. Cook for 1 minute, mixing everything. Add tomatoes and 1/8 tsp of turmeric to the pan. Cook covered for 1 minute or until the tomatoes soften. Crack one egg in a bowl and add  1 tbsp milk and 1/3 tsp salt. Whisk the egg mixture in the bowl. Slowly pour the whisked eggs into the pan. Keep mixing with a spatula for 3 minutes or until the eggs are almost cooked. Garnish with 1 tbsp chopped cilantro and serve.
